<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qinghua Graduate School Established in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Construction began today on the
Qinghua Graduate School in Shenzhen, the booming border city in
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The project was launched by the city as part of the nationwide
effort to invigorate the country's research resources and develop
the hi-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
Under the cooperation agreement between the city government and
Qinghua University, the graduate school will consist of
engineering research centers and laboratories for studies in a
variety of fields, including information projects, biological
medicine and new materials.
</P>
<P>
The school will train a large number of high-level scientific
or managerial personnel for the city.
</P>
<P>
Construction will be completed in early 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
