<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rail Line in Southern Xinjiang Extended Westward </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The first section of track
extending the railway line in southern Xinjiang to the west was
laid today.
</P>
<P>
The project, launched in September 1996, involves construction
of a 975-km railway line from Korla to Kashi, a westward entension
of the southern rail line in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
which runs 475 km from Turpan to Korla.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the project, which will be complete in three and
a half years, stands at 5.87 billion yuan (about 700 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Almost half of the region's population live in southern
Xinjiang, where a group of bases of China's commodities such as
oil, cotton, grain, and petro-chemicals are being built.
</P>
<P>
With a transportation capacity of 15 million tons, the new
longer rail line will further promote the exploitation of oil and
natural gas resources in the Tarim Basin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
