<HEADLINE> Weifang Opens 14th Kite Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIFANG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The 14th Annual Weifang Kite
Festival opened today in Shandong Province in the eastern part of
China, the country where the high-flying sport is said to have
originated.
</P>
<P>
Various kite contests will be held throughout the festival, a
major sporting event for kite fans throughout the country and
regarded by the province as an important chance for carrying out
exchanges with foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Kite-flying teams from the USA, India, Malaysia, New Zealand,
Hong Kong and Taiwan will attend the festival, together with kite
fans from 20 provinces and autonomous regions in China. 
