<HEADLINE> World Cup Swimming Calendar for 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOTHENBURG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 World Cup swimming
will comprise nine venues, one more than this year, the sports
world governing body FINA said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Swimmers can score points at a maximum of five venues, of which
only three can be on the same continent.
</P>
<P>
Following is the calendar:
</P>
<P>
January 21-22: An Australian East Coast venue
</P>
<P>
February 21-22: Hong Kong
</P>
<P>
February 25-26: Beijing
</P>
<P>
March 7-8: Rio de Janeiro
</P>
<P>
March 13-14: Sheffield, England
</P>
<P>
March 17-18: Malmo, Sweden
</P>
<P>
March 21-22: Gelsenkirchen, Germany
</P>
<P>
March 25-26: An Italian venue, tentatively Imperia
</P>
<P>
March 28-29: Paris
</P>
</TEXT>
