<HEADLINE> Gujral 2ndadd: Gujral to Be Sworn in as PM Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Inder Kumar Gujral will be
sworn in tomorrow as India's 12th prime minister by President
Shanker Dayal Sharma who directed him to seek a vote of confidence
in the Lok Sabha (the lower house of parliament) by April 22, the
Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
The appointment of Gujral, who will head a 16-party United
Front (UF) coalition, came within less than 12 hours of his
unanimous election as leader of the UF parliamentary party earlier
in the day.
</P>
<P>
The requisite oath of office and secrecy is scheduled to be
administered at 10:00 hours tomorrow morning, an hour before the
Indian Parliament meets for a special session to pass the budget
for 1997-98.
</P>
<P>
The 78-year-old Janata Dal veteran, who was asked by the
president to give the names of those to be included in the Council
of Ministers, told reporters at the Presidential Palace here that
he will finalize the list tonight.  
</P>
</TEXT>
