<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foshan Ties Tianjin in CFA Cup Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Foshan Fosidi forced a 1-1 tie
against Tianjin Samsung in its opening match of the Chinese
Football Association (CAF) Cup in Foshan, Guangdong Province on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Foshan, a second-division side, surprised first-division club
Samsung with concerted fast attacks from the beginning and had
several scoring chances in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Foshan opened the scoring in the last minute of the first half,
when Shao Aiming headed the ball past goaltender Shi Lianzhi into
the net on a Zhang Lei pass.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin levelled it 1-1 in the 81st minute through Yu Genwei.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Henan Jianye lost to Qingdao Hainiu 2-3,
Tianjin Wanke drew with Guangzhou Apollo 1-1, and Vanguards
Huandao quashed Shenzhen Ping'an 4-1.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Jinpeng beat Shanghai Yuyuan 2-1, Locomotive tied
August First 0-0, Shenyang Haishi beat Wuhan Yaqi 4-2 and Yanbian
Aodong lost to Liaoning 0-1. 
</P>
