<HEADLINE> URGENT: Israeli Prosecutor Drop Indictment Against Netanyahu (By Zhi Linfei &AMP; Huai Chengbo) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Attorney General
Elyakim Rubinstein annouced today not to indict Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu for his alleged involvement in the Bar-On
scandal.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference in Jerusalem together with
State Attorney Edana Arbel and other senior police and justice
officials, Rubinstein said that no indictment would be filed
against Netanyahu as well as Justice Minister Tzahi Hanegbi
for lack of solid evidence in the police recommendations.
</P>
