<HEADLINE> Floods Kill 23, Injure 22 Others in Ethiopia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Floods resulted from heavy
rain have killed 23 people and injured 22 others in Ethiopia's
southwestern town of Arba Minch, a report from the Ethiopian News
Agency said today.
</P>
<P>
The report said, most of the victims were children. The bodies
of many people were found some 5 kms away from their localities.
</P>
<P>
"The death toll could increase because rocks rolled by the
floods from the nearby basin have crushed the houses of many
people," said the report by quoting local administrators.
</P>
<P>
The local police and members of the riot police with the
support of the general public are continuing to look for more
corpses, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The rain that fell on Saturday destroyed many residential
units and damaged property whose value is not yet known. Electric
and telephone lines in the town were dismantled by the floods.
</P>
</TEXT>
