<HEADLINE> Molotov Cocktails Blast in Greek Military Parking Lot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Two molotov cocktails exploded in
a Greek military parking lot here today, causing a bus completely
destroyed and two jeeps slightly damaged.
</P>
<P>
So far, there have been no reports of injuries.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred in the capital suburb of Goudi early this
morning, according to a Greek army general staff announcement
today.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
This is the second attack which targeted the Greek military
properties within a week.
</P>
<P>
On April 16, an explosion on a train in the suburb of Aghioi
Anargyri, west of Athens, damaged two army vehicles just before
the first Greek troops left for the strife-ridden Albania later in
the day.
</P>
<P>
Greece has decided to send troops to participate in the
Italian-led multinational force to Albania for securing the
distribution of humanitarian aid there. 
