<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier's Speech at PATA Annual Conference (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To speed up the development of tourism constitutes an important
component of the outline for national economic and social
development for the last five years of this century and the first
ten years of next century formulated by the Chinese
Government. Our overall objectives are to vigorously develop and
fully utilize tourism resources, effectively develop scenic spots
and improve support tourism facilities, step up management and
provide quality service with a view to accelerating the
development of both domestic and international tourism. To this
end,
</P>
<P>
We will continue to put tourism industry at an important
position, formulate corresponding supporting policies, fully
mobilize the initiative of various parties and promote the
development of tourism at an accelerated pace in regions with
sound conditions;
</P>
<P>
We will further improve tourism transportation, step up
tourism infrastructure building, speed up the development of
diverse tourism products, strive to improve the quality of service
with a view to raising the overall level of the tourism industry;
</P>
<P>
We will attach even greater importance to the promotive role of
the tourism industry, speed up the development of those sectors
related to tourism, make greater efforts in developing tourism in
remote areas with rich tourism resources and use it to promote the
overall economic and social progress of the regions concerned;
</P>
<P>
We will energetically develop a variety of tourism resources
and at the same time, properly handle the relationship between
resource development and environmental and ecological protection
with a view to achieving a coordinated development of tourism,
environment and economy;
</P>
<P>
We will step up exchanges and cooperation with international
tourism organizations and tourism communities of other
countries. And in particular, we will intensify our cooperation in
such fields as product development, marketing promotion, personnel
training, and tourism management, and learn from each other for
common improvement so as to facilitate the prosperity of the
international tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
We are confident that China's economic growth and social
progress will open up new vistas for the development of China's
tourism industry.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970421.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uzbekistan Joins U.N. Program to Benefit Disabled People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Uzbekistan has signed a document
to join a United Nations regional program for providing more
benefits to people with disabilities.
</P>
<P>
The program, said an Itar-Tass news agency report from Tashkent
today, stems from a U.N. proclamation calling for the full
participation and equality of disabled people.
</P>
<P>
By endorsing the document, Uzbek Social Protection Minister
Bakhodyr Umurzakov was quoted as saying, the country would join
the international community in protecting the disabled.
</P>
<P>
The move made Uzbekistan eligible for 240,000 U.S. dollars from
the U.N. Economic and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific
(ESCAP) for creating 5,000 job positions for disabled people.
</P>
<P>
Umurzakov noted that the Uzbek government is carrying out its
own 1996-2000 program for protecting disabled people.
</P>
<P>
Five rehabilitation centers are scheduled for opening within
this year to provide social, medical and labor assistance to over
50,000 people in the Central Asian country, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Also this year, he added, about 30,000 disabled people will
have an opportunity to spend holidays at state-owned health
centers and holiday hotels for free. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
