<HEADLINE> Hewlett Packard, IBM Top List of Vendors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Hewlett-Packard and IBM, two
leading computer makers of the U.S., rated the best in overall
customer satisfaction among server and software vendors, according
to a Computerworld customer satisfaction survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey asked customers to evaluate vendors who offer
medium- to large-scale hardware platforms and system-level
software like systems management tools and database management
systems.
</P>
<P>
Each vendor was ranked in terms of product quality, service and
support, cost of ownership and general comfort in doing business
with the vendor.
</P>
<P>
The overall satisfaction reported on a scale of 1 to 5, where 5
is "completely satisfied," is as follows: Hewlett-Packard, 3.91;
IBM, 3.86; Dell, 3.85; Compaq, 3.80; Sun, 3.78; Digital, 3.74; and
Unisys, 3.70.
</P>
<P>
Other findings of the survey include:
</P>
<P>
-- IBM scored respectable marks in mainframes, and the AS/400
received the highest user satisfaction grades in distributed
systems;
</P>
<P>
-- Dell Computer Corporation held an edge over PC-based server
rival Compaq Computer Corporation in most categories, but
especially in price and value;
</P>
<P>
-- Computer Associates International, Inc. scored dismally low
in its three core business sectors: mainframe DBMS; mainframe
tools and utilities; and distributed systems management software.
</P>
<P>
The survey was mailed to 4,000 corporations and large
organizations selected from Computerworld's buyers' database.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
