<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier's Speech at PATA Annual Conference (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The following is the full text of
a speech entitled "Enhancing International Exchanges and
Cooperation, Promoting All-round Development of Tourism Industry,"
delivered by Chinese Premier Li Peng at the Opening Ceremony of an
annual conference of the Pacific Asia Travel Association (PATA)
held here today:

Delegates,
Guests,
Ladies and Gentlemen,
Friends,
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of the opening of the 46th Annual Conference of
PATA in Beijing today, I'd like to extend, on behalf of the
Chinese Government and people, our warm welcome to all the
delegates and guests present, and our warm congratulations on the
convocation of the conference.
</P>
<P>
As a highly comprehensive sector in the modern economy, the
tourism industry is not only part and parcel of the global
economy, but also an important symbol of the improvement of
people's livelihood in the modern era. To develop tourism is of
great significance in promoting the friendly exchanges among
people of all countries, deepening the mutual understanding and
friendship among them and accelerating economic growth and social
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Looking into the 21st century, we believe that the tourism
industry boasts broad prospects for its future development and
will offer more job opportunities to all the countries, thereby
becoming a major driving force in advancing world economy. In
recent years, with its rapid growth, tourism in the Asia-Pacific
region is holding an increasingly prominent position in the world
tourism industry. As a member of the Asia-Pacific, China is ready
to make positive contributions to the development of tourism in
this region and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Being a multi-ethnic country with a vast territory and a long
history of several millennia, China abounds in tourism resources
with its beautiful natural scenery, numerous places of historic
interest and cultural sites and its splendid and colorful
culture. Since reform and opening-up, China has enjoyed a
sustained economic growth, averaging nearly 10 percent per year, a
vigorous development of all its undertakings and a marked rise in
its people's living standards. All this constitutes a solid
foundation for the prosperity in its tourism industry. China's
political stability, economic growth and market prosperity, and
the Chinese Government's opening-up endeavor and its active
efforts to develop its relations with other countries in the world
have also helped create favorable conditions for the development
of tourism. Attaching great importance to tourism, the Chinese
Government has accorded priority to tourism in the development of
the tertiary industries. It has made constant efforts in
developing its tourism resources, improving tourism facilities and
enhancing service quality, thus promoting the speedy development
of tourism both at home and abroad. In 1996, China received over
51 million overseas tourists. Domestic tourists amounted to 640
million person/times. At the same time, as the living standards of
the Chinese people continue to improve, the number of Chinese
people traveling abroad is increasing year by year, which has
instilled fresh vitality into the development of the international
tourism industry.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970421.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier's Speech at PATA Annual Conference (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This year has been designated as the "Visit China '97"
year. The Chinese Government will give its full support to ensure
the success of this event and will help create better conditons
for promoting the development of China's tourism and the
cooperation between China's tourism community and that of the
world. We hope more friends from overseas will come to China as
tourists and see with their own eyes China's famous mountains,
great rivers and other places of historical interest and scenic
spots, as well as the great changes that have taken place in China
since reform and opening-up. This will contribute to the
enhancement of our mutual understanding and friendship.
</P>
<P>
As an important international tourism organization, PATA has,
over the years, played a positive role in promoting the
development and cooperation in the tourism industry in the
Asia-Pacific region and the world as a whole. During this Annual
Conference, the participants will conduct extensive and in-depth
discussions on a variety of important issues concerning the future
development of the tourism industry. I am convinced that with the
joint efforts of all the participants, this Conference will yield
positive results and push further ahead the development of tourism
in this region and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
I would like to conclude by wishing this Annual Conference of
PATA will be a crowning success!
</P>
<P>
Thank you.
</P>
</TEXT>
