<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
met here today with a Japanese delegation from Nippon Steel
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that Nippon Steel Corporation of Japan, the largest
enterprise producing iron and steel, has conducted fruitful
cooperation with China in the last two decades, believing that the
visit will further enhance the bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Wu also briefed the guests on the reform and opening up drive
and economic development in China, saying that the political
stability and continuous, rapid and healthy economic advancement
will provide sound conditions for Sino-Japan cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Wu welcomed Japan to participate in restructuring China's old
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Takashi Imai, President of Nippon Steel Corporation, said that
the rapid development of China's iron and steel industry impressed
him deeply, adding that Nippon Steel Corporation is willing to
serve the development of China's iron and steel industries with
its advanced technology and hopes to tap new fields for
cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese guests arrived here as guests of the Ministry of
Metallurgical Industry.  
</P>
