<HEADLINE> Johansson Backs German Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- UEFA president Lennart Johansson
hopes England will withdraw their bid for the 2006 World Cup,
European football's Swedish head told the Frankfurter Allgemeine
Zeitung on Monday.
</P>
<P>
UEFA, who Johansson insists came to a gentleman's agreement
over England staging the 1996 European Championships and Germany
bidding for the 2006 World Cup, withdrew their public support for
Germany last week.
</P>
<P>
However, the Germans, who had been convinced they would be the
sole European candidate, will have taken heart from Johansson's
backing.
</P>
<P>
"The English are going to get worried the day they see we keep
our word," he said.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, Argentina, South Africa, Egypt and Morocco have already
announced they will be bidding for the 2006 tournament. The
winner will be named by FIFA, the world's governing body, in
2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
