<HEADLINE> Ramos Orders Intensified Drive Against Gunrunning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today ordered Interior and Local Governments Secretary Robert
Barbers to step up the campaign against arms trafficking and
gunrunning in the country.
</P>
<P>
Ramos made the directive in the wake of an earlier newspaper
report claiming that Muslim rebels in the southern Philippines
were buying arms like "fish from the market."
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Al Haj Murad, military chief of the Moro
Islamic Liberation Front, as saying "it's as easy as buying fish
from the market" for the MILF to acquire arms and ammunition.
</P>
<P>
The president tasked Barbers and Defense Secretary Renato de
Villa to come up with a joint program to crack down on arms
traffickers.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also asked them to submit their first progress report on
the actions they have taken not later than May 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The MILF is a breakaway faction of the mainstream Moro National
Liberation Front (MNLF) which signed a peace deal with the
government last September.
</P>
<P>
The MILF has been engaged with the government forces in
sporadic fighting in Mindanao island, the southern Philippines,
since early last week.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the military confirmed that the renewed fighting
killed 25 MILF rebels and two soldiers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
