<HEADLINE> Nepal Wants Foreign Investment in Transport Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Nepal today called on foreign
investors for some alternative transportation means in the country
as the country's existing road system is facing the ever-growing
pressure.
</P>
<P>
The government invited foreign investment to build and operate
three routes of trolley bus services, respectively in eastern,
mid-western and western regions, a press release of the Ministry
of Works and Transport said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government also called on foreign investors for
developing two new highway projects near Kathmandu and running
taxi service operations in certain areas of the country, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
As Nepal has utilized few alternative transport facilities so
far, the government wants the foreign private sector's
participation in the development and expansion of the country's
transport sector, the press release said.  
</P>
