<HEADLINE> NPC Leader Meets Kazakhstan Parliament Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here this
evening with a delegation of the Parliament of Kazakhstan, led by
its lower house chairman Marat Ospanov.
</P>
<P>
Qiao welcomed Marat and his party, saying China and Kazakhstan
are friendly neighboring countries and the bilateral good ties
have grown stronger since the two countries forged diplomatic
relations in 1992.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized China attaches great importance to its
relationship with Kazakhstan and treasures the existing friendship
between the two countries and their people.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the Kazakhstan entrepreneurs and
media accompanying Marat will gain an greater understanding of
China from their current visit.
</P>
<P>
"The NPC and the Kazakhstan parliament play important roles in
domestic affairs and in building long-term good-neighborly
relations between China and Kazakhstan. We believe that the
current visit will contribute to developing a sound and stable
bilateral relations and to strengthening the friendly cooperation
between the two legislatures," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the visitors on China's achievements since it
carried out reform and opening up policies 18 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Ospanov said the delegation members are pleased for the
opportunity to visit China and they will make the most of their
chance to learn more about China's experience in reform and NPC's
working experience.
</P>
<P>
He said the experience is precious to Kazakhstan and both
Kazakhstan congressmen and people from various circles hope to
draw on the success of China's economic construction.
</P>
<P>
There is no obstacle to developing Kazakhstan-Chinese friendly
cooperation and the contact between the Kazakhstan parliament and
the NPC will help further develop bilateral relations, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Ospanov invited Qiao to visit Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived here this afternoon on an official
goodwill visit to China, as guests of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
</P>
