<HEADLINE> 12 Soldiers Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Twelve government soldiers today
were killed when Tamil rebels attacked them in Northern province,
according to military sources here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that a route clearing patrol sent out from
Kumburumulla detachment was attacked by a group of Tamil rebels at
Valachchenai in Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated and the rebels withdrew with their
casualties. However, at least 12 soldiers were killed during the
confrontation, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year old guerrilla war
for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the island
country.  
