<HEADLINE> Austrian Ski Body to Mull Punishment Against Goldberger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian Ski Federation (OSV)
said it would decide on Monday how to discipline ski jumper
Andreas Goldberger who admitted to using cocaine.
</P>
<P>
Goldberger, 25, overall World Cup ski jumping in 1995 and 1996,
on Sunday told an Austrian television station that he used the
drug at a Vienna disco a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Goldberger denied he was addicted to the drug and regularly
bought it, but said curiosity drove him to "try it once".
</P>
<P>
The Austrian news agency APA on Monday quoted OSV President
Peter Schroecksnadel that the federation had temporarily suspended
Goldberger until a disciplinary board meeting on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
