<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Continued strength in the
banking sector and an improved performance from gold stocks pushed
a lackluster Australian share market marginally higher today.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed 3.4 points higher at
2445.8, while the all industrials index climbed 3.6 points to
3847.6 and the all resources index added 3.6 points to 1364.9.
</P>
<P>
Market interest centered on gold junior Carpenter Pacific and
Australia's most profitable bank, National Australia Bank, which
soared 1.73 percent, or 28.5 cents, as buyers anticipated another
bumper profit performance due next month.
</P>
<P>
The banking index rose 37.1 points to 4245.9, with ANZ
improving 7.7 cents, Commonwealth Bank rising five cents and
Westpac ending steady.
</P>
<P>
The gold index rose 15.1 points to 1597.9.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 294.26 million shares valued at
521.93 million Australian dollars (404.5 million US dollars).
</P>
