<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Uruguayan Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
held talks here today with Uruguayan President Julio Maria
Sanguinetti, saying that China and Latin American countries will
work together to safeguard world peace and stability and to
promote development that will benefit both sides.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Great Hall of the People, Jiang
welcomed Sanguinetti, who is on his visit to China as president,
and pointed out that he is the only Latin American state leader
who had met with late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China will never forget Sanguinetti's efforts
to normalize the relations between China and Uruguay during his
presidential term nine years ago. He expressed his pleasure over
meeting Sanguinetti again after their first meeting in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Sanguinetti thanked the Chinese government and the Chinese
people for their warm welcome to him on his third trip to
China. He met with Deng Xiaoping in 1988, during his visit to
China in 1988.
</P>
<P>
He said that he and the Uruguayan people held Deng Xiaoping in
high esteem, and considered him one of the greatest men of the
modern world. He also congratulated China on continuing to take a
correct development path.
</P>
<P>
Jiang offered a positive assessment of the progress in
relations between the two countries, pointing out that the ties
have advanced smoothly since the diplomatic relations were
forged. Contacts between high-ranking officials of the two
countries have played an irreplaceable role in the development of
bilateral, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China attaches great importance to its relations
with Uruguay. China is glad to see that in recent years, Uruguay
has achieved political stability and economic growth, and that it
has played an important role in regional and world affairs,
especially in the process of regional integration, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he appreciated Uruguay's efforts to back China's
entry into the World Trade Organization (WTO) and the America
Development Bank (ADB), to actively promote the establishment of a
dialogue framework between China and the Latin American countries,
to adhere to the "one China" stand on the Taiwan question, and to
provide understanding and support to China on the human rights
issue.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is ready to serve as a bridge for exchanges
between Uruguay and the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
