<DOCNO> XIE19970421.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Uruguayan Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sanguinetti spoke highly of the fruitful bilateral ties based
on mutual trust, pointing out that the two countries have become
reliable cooperative partners.
</P>
<P>
He said that there is a trend of multi-polarization in the
world. Since China is playing an important role in the world, he
added, Uruguay is giving priority to its relations with China and
would like both sides to continue to support each other in
international affairs and expand bilateral ties in various fields,
including trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that although the economic cooperation of the two
countries is in the early stage, the development trend is good.
</P>
<P>
China would like to explore new fields and patterns of
cooperation with Uruguay, Jiang said, adding that many businessmen
accompanying Sanguinetti on his current visit can provide numerous
opportunities for exchange with the Chinese business circle.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the governments of the two countries
will encourage the cooperation between the enterprises of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
With the development of China's economy, China's foreign trade
and economic cooperation with other countries will advance at a
greater rate, Jiang said, and as a result there are bright
prospects for the economic cooperation between China and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China is pleased to see that Latin American
countries have been more aware of the importance of unity,
cooperation and opposition to power politics, and that the
integration process of Latin America is growing rapidly.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his hope that the Latin American countries will
make more progress in increasing economic prosperity and social
development, and eliminating poverty.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Latin American countries, all still
developing, have much common ground, and China would like to
strengthen cooperation with them to safeguard peace and promote
mutual development.
</P>
<P>
Sanguinetti briefed Jiang on the trade and economic cooperation
among Latin American countries, especially the growth of Mercosur,
adding that such cooperation has political significance.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China's presence in Mercosur is very
important, and his country will help Chinese businesses to enter
Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
Sanguinetti extended an official invitation to Jiang to visit
Uruguay, which the Chinese president accepted.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two presidents attended a signing ceremony
for three cooperative documents between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Jiang presided over a welcoming ceremony in
honor of Sanguinetti, who arrived here Sunday evening for a state
visit to China at Jiang's invitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
