<HEADLINE> Jakarta Sends Black Box of Ill-Fated Jet to Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Merpati Nusantara
Airlines has sent its ill-fated plane's black box to Australia for
analysis, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The black box, which was found early Sunday, has been sent to
Australia as the country is considered a leading expert on black
box technology, Transportation Minister Haryano Dhanutirto said.
</P>
<P>
A Merpati plane carrying 53 people on board crashed in Belitung
island, South Sumatra, last Saturday, killing 15 of the passengers
while injuring 31 others.
</P>
<P>
The government has ordered Merpati to ground its remaining
fleet of British-made advanced Turbo prop (ATP) aircraft after the
accident.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the minister acknowledged that the supply of spare
parts for the ATP planes used by Merpati has not seen smooth.
</P>
<P>
As a result three of the five ATPs used by the state-owned
airline company are now grounded, he said.
</P>
<P>
Merpati Nusantara which has a fleet of over 100 airplanes
mainly serve domestic routes.  
</P>
