<HEADLINE> ADB to Host Workshop on Philippine Local Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
said here today that it will hold a workshop aiming at
strengthening its ties with Philippine local government units at
its headquarters in Manila on April 24-25.
</P>
<P>
The workshop is part of a series of activities on best
practices of local government units jointly financed by the ADB
and the Ford Foundation.
</P>
<P>
During the workshop, representatives from the national and
local governments, non-government organizations and donor agencies
will exchange views with bank staff.
</P>
<P>
The results of the workshop will feed into the banks' upcoming
new Country Operational Strategy for the Philippines, which is
suggesting a gradual shift of the bank from growth-promoting
investments towards a growth-with-equity approach.
</P>
<P>
Based on this new country strategy, the bank will emphasize in
its future programs the delivery of social, communal,
environmental and infrastructure services to support poverty
reduction and sustainable development in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
For this purpose, the workshop will recommend new forms of
cooperation between the national and local governments and the
bank for most of its future activities.  
</P>
