<HEADLINE> ADB Operations Slightly Increase in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
increased its total operations last year to 5.8 billion U.S.
dollars from 5.7 billion the previous year, according to the
bank's annual report released here today.
</P>
<P>
The total figure includes loans, equity investments and
technical assistance grants, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The bank's loan to the public and private sectors amounted to
5.5 billion U.S. dollars for 83 projects last year, less than one
percent higher than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, equity investments totaling 107 million
U.S. dollars were made in 10 companies while technical assistance
grants rose by just over 20 percent to 175 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Although the loan amount rose only slightly, the report said,
there was a significant rise in the number of loans, from 74 in
1995 to 92 last year.
</P>
<P>
The first loan was also approved to Uzbekistan which joined the
bank in 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
