<DOCNO> XIE19970421.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao's External Trade Up in 1st 2 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Both Macao's imports and exports
stepped out of the doldrums in the first two months of the year,
rising by more than 6 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that the exports reached 2.3 billion patacas
(about 291 million US dollars), up 10.5 percent from the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The value of imports hit 2.2 billion patacas (about 278 million
US dollars), up 6.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
As a result, a trade surplus of 108 million patacas (about
13.67 million US dollars) was recorded. That was 2.91 times the
figure of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the export value of textile and garment products,
which account for 84.8 percent of all exports, rose 20 percent,
while the exports of non-textile products, including machinery,
footwear and cement, dropped 23.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The United States and the European Union, Macao's leading
export markets, bought 78.2 percent of all Macao export goods.
</P>
<P>
The main import market is still in the Asian-Pacific region,
including the Chinese mainland, Taiwan, Japan and Australia, which
in a row have recorded import growth.
</P>
<P>
But imports from the Republic of Korea and Hong Kong have
declined 20.8 percent and 1.2 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Imports from the United States, European Union, Britain and
Germany also decreased.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
