<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Kick off Major Gas Pipeline Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will kick off a major gas
pipeline project next month that will bring rich natural gas from
oil fields in the south to industrial areas in the southwest.
</P>
<P>
The Business Times reported today that the project will cost
26 million U.S. Dollars and will be completed by July next year.
</P>
<P>
It will serve the Ikeja and Isolo industrial areas in Lagos
and the Agbara industrial area in the neighboring Ogun state,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The pipeline will be extended to other west African countries
in the future, as being planned by the governments.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has rich natural gas resources, but a large sum of
them are being flared daily at many oil fields.
</P>
<P>
A senior official of the Nigerian Gas Company said natural gas
will serve as an ideal alternative source of energy to
enterprises in the said industrial areas where power supply has
been poor and unreliable.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the use of natural gas in two plants of the
West African Portland Cement Company has resulted in higher
productivity and lower cost. 
</P>
</TEXT>
