<HEADLINE> 410 Houses Lost in Fire in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Some 410 houses were destroyed
today in a fire that hit the crowded coastal community of Ermita
in Cebu city, the second biggest city in the central Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which brought about a loss of five million pesos
(190,000 U.S. dollars) in properties, was believed to have started
on the second floor of a house occupied by Ermita Councilor
Reynardo Cellan.
</P>
<P>
It took firefighters 30 minutes to control the fire which
started this morning. A 60-year-old woman suffered second degree
burns on her face and hands.
</P>
<P>
Cebu city fire investigator Fortunato Buscia said the cause of
the blaze is still being determined.
</P>
<P>
In October last year, some 200 houses in the same place were
also razed in fire.  
</P>
