<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks Trading Suspended Due to Power Failure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Trading at the Philippine Stock
Exchange was suspended here today after a power failure occurred
at the East Tower Building where the Exchange holds its regular
trading.
</P>
<P>
The power failure at the same time forced thousands of
employees, including brokers and officials, to be left with no
choice but to stay outside since early hours this morning.
</P>
<P>
Carmelita Rapal, spokesperson of the building's administration
office, said the situation is now under control after the
technicians were able to immediately attend to the generator which
eventually overheated on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
However, another employee who requested not to be named said
that transactions will no longer be possible today owing to the
continuous repair work on the electrical system.
</P>
<P>
The Exchange building is divided into the West Tower Building
and East Tower Building. Many are surprised as to why only the
east one where the stock exchange is housed was affected by the
power failure.
</P>
<P>
Rapal said that the maintenance department of the building
informed all the offices inside that there would be a power
shutdown owing to an impending repair work on the electrical
system of the building.
</P>
<P>
But a disgruntled broker said that he really does not know the
motive behind the power failure.
</P>
<P>
This is not the first time that power problems have taken place
at the Stock Exchange building. Computer problems also often
caused fire failure in the building, said a broker.
</P>
<P>
Stock market analysts expressed disappointment over the
suspension of the stock trading as this will mean millions of
pesos of losses to the trading floors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
