<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mayors of Old Chinese Towns Meet in Northern City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUOYANG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The mayors of more than 20
Chinese cities, each with a long history, have come to Luoyang
City in Henan Province, for a three-day forum on how to protect
the historic cultural heritage.
</P>
<P>
The cities include Beijing, Lhasa, Nanjing, Guangzhou,
Hangzhou, Suzhou, Yangzhou, Qufu, Kaifeng, Xi'an and Luoyang.
</P>
<P>
The forum, the "First Forum of Mayors from Well-Known Historic
and Cultural Cities in China", will focus on ways of opening up
old towns to the outside world and the relationship between
economic development and protection of cultural relics.
</P>
<P>
Luoyang is now hosting the 15th Luoyang Peony Fair, which runs
from April 15 to 25. The city is one of China's oldest capitals
and is known for its long history of raising peonies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
