<HEADLINE> Chinese Newsmen And Educators' Environmental Work Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Six eminent newsmen and educators
won awards today for their environmental protection efforts.
</P>
<P>
An "Earth Prize" was set up by the China Environment Newsmen's
Association and a Hong Kong group, "Friends of the Earth" to
encourage people to donate efforts to environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The six winners were chosen from a total of 209 candidates from
28 province-level organizations. The eldest, Yu Yunxian, 67, has
been working to develop environmental education in elementary and
middle schools.
</P>
<P>
Xie Zhenhua, director of the State Bureau of Environmental
Protection, thanked the recipients for their work to promote
awareness of the environment among the public.
</P>
<P>
China's remarkable progress in environmental protection is
closely associated with the participation of the public, Xie said.
</P>
<P>
