<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Alert Causes Travel Chaos in  London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Five London railway stations and
parts of Heathrow and Gatwick airports closed today in a series of
bomb warnings.
</P>
<P>
Police said the central London railway stations were evacuated
and surrounding roads were closed after they received a number of
"threatening phone calls."
</P>
<P>
Parts of Heathrow airport were closed off, and the Gatwick
airport train station and Stansted airport were also shut as a
result of the warnings.
</P>
<P>
Police warned people not to travel to central London if
possible. But hundreds of thousands of people were already
stranded on trains, stuck in traffic jams or forced behind police
barriers on the streets.
</P>
<P>
"This is causing massive disruption. It has been timed just as
the morning rush hour is about to hit its peak," a railtrack
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The security alert followed two Irish Republican Army (IRA)
bomb blasts and warnings last Friday which paralyzed road and rail
systems in northern England.
</P>
<P>
The IRA has stepped up its campaign against British rule in
Northern Ireland in the runup to the May 1 national election.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
