<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong, Macao Trade Unions to Mark Labor Day in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Over 300 members of Hong Kong and
Macao trade unions will celebrate International Labor Day on May 1
in Beijing at the invitation of the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions (ACFTU).
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Federation of Trade Unions (HKFTU), the largest
labor organization in Hong Kong, will have a 320-member delegation
to mark Hong Kong's return to the motherland. The Hong Kong
Trade Union and Macao Trade Union will also send delegations.
</P>
<P>
Ni Haomei, ACFTU vice-chairperson, said at today's press
conference that the Hong Kong and Macao delegates will have a
chance to visit factories, rural villages, and military
installations during their stay.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong and Macao visitors will also attend a national flag
raising ceremony on Tiananmen Square on May 1, and workers from
Beijing will hold a get-together with Hong Kong and Macao guests.
</P>
<P>
This is the first activity of its kind to be held by the
ACFTU. Ni expressed the hope that Hong Kong workers can learn more
about workers on the mainland and that they will be encouraged to
work for the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong after it
returns to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
HKFTU has 116 affiliates with a total membership of 250,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
