<HEADLINE> Ten Outstanding Chinese Workers Selected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A deaf-mute person who is still
working at the age of 58 has become one of China's "10 Outstanding
Workers" this year.
</P>
<P>
Li Shaoyan has been a fitter for 40 years at the Anshan
Transportation Machinery Plant, a welfare factory in northeast
China's Liaoning province. His hard work and diligence have made a
quiet contribution to the factory.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 18 years, he saved the factory some 10,000 yuan
annually, and some equipment he developed increased efficiency
50-fold.
</P>
<P>
Li's fellow winners include a women driver, Jiang Zaiying, who
is driving a 34-ton truck at the Three Gorges construction site;
Niu Xingzhuang, the member of a drilling crew at the Dagang
Oilfield in Tianjin; Kang Longtian, a miner from China's largest
coking coal base; and Li Bin, a young worker from the Shanghai
Hydraulic Pump Plant.
</P>
<P>
Five of the ten are national model workers and the other five
are winners of "May 1" Labor Medal, the top award for Chinese
workers.
</P>
<P>
The "Ten Outstanding Workers" were chosen by the All-China
Federation of trade Unions (ACFTU).
</P>
<P>
Li and the others will be invited by the ACFTU to participate
in the celebration activities for the International Labor's Day in
Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
