<HEADLINE> Chinese PM Congratulates India's New PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng today
sent a congratulatory message to India's new prime minister Inder
Kumar Gujral on the occasion of his assumption of office.
</P>
<P>
Extending warm congratulations to Gujral, Premier Li hailed the
profound friendship between China and India.
</P>
<P>
"It is the common aspiration of the two governments and two
peoples to build Sino-Indian future-oriented constructive and
cooperative partnership," he said in the message.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li said "To establish Sino-Indian friendly and
good-neighbourly relations and mutually-beneficial cooperation on
the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence not only
serves the fundamental interests of the two peoples, but also
peace and stability in the region and the rest of the world."
</P>
<P>
He expressed sincere hope that during Inder Kumar Gujral's
tenure of office "Sino-Indian relationship, on the existing basis,
register greater successes."
</P>
<P>
Gujral, 77, was chosen Saturday to replace former prime
minister H.D.Deve Gowda who lost a confidence vote last month.
