<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwandan Refugees in Uganda Repatriated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commission for Refugees ) and the Ugandan government today
started to repatriate Rwandan refugees.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper "the New Vision" reported today that some 500
refugees registered with the UNHCR are to be repatriated.
</P>
<P>
The Hutu refugees of Rwanda had sought asylum in southwestern
Uganda when the Tutsi-led Rwandan Patriotic Front entered Rwanda
from Uganda in 1990. They concentrated in Orukinga Refugee
Resettlement Camp in Mbarara, southwestern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Some refugees fearing repatriation are trying to hide in the
families of their relatives in southwestern districts of Mbarara
and Masaka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
