<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Increase Amount of Rural Housing by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- China plans to build three
billion sq m of rural housing by the end of the century to meet
the need for better housing among the country's rural residents.
</P>
<P>
Some five percent of the country's total rural households will
build new houses before the end of the century, according to the
Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
A source there says that, with the rapid development of the
rural economy, rural residents' desire for better housing has
increased, and annual housing construction now exceeds 600 million
sq m.
</P>
<P>
Average per capita housing in rural areas has gone from 17.8 sq
m in 1985 to 22 sq m now, and 100 million houses have been built
in the country's rural areas over the past five years, with nearly
half of the country's rural households moving or having moved into
new housing, the source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
