<HEADLINE> Thailand to Host 17th Asian Women's Basketball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The 17th Asian Women's Basketball
Championship will be held from April 27 to May 5 in Bangkok, the
Asian Basketball Confederation announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Mauricio Martelino, secretary general of Asian basketball
governing body, said that 14 countries and regions had confirmed
their participation in the championships.
</P>
<P>
The 14 teams will be divided into two groups. Group A includes
defending champions China, last championship runners-up South
Korea and Japan, Chinese Taipei, Kyrgyzstan and hosts Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The top three finishers of Group A will qualify for next year's
world championship in Germany.
</P>
<P>
The other eight teams will be grouped in Group B. They are
Malaysia, Indonesia, India, Sri Lanka, Hong Kong, Macao, Singapore
and Kazakhstan. The top two teams of the group will be promoted
into Group A in the next edition of the championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
