<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 07:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Indonesia Plan to Open New Air Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Indonesia will
open a new air route to expand commercial cooperation between the
two countries and meet the increasing demands of exchanges in
various fields, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said Kuwaiti Airways Corporation, the only
state-run airways company in the country, was currently
discussing plans to open a new route to the Indonesian
island of Bali, the second destination of the company in
Indonesia after Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
They said talks are being held with a delegation from the
Indonesian airline Garuda. A number of essential issues were
covered, including strengthening commercial cooperation between
the two national carriers.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed the expansion of cooperation to
include new destinations and cities to be covered by commercial
arrangements in the future.
</P>
<P>
One official from the Kuwait Airways Corporation told Xinhua
that the idea of opening the route was to "make the island of
Bali as a second stop after the capital of Jakarta in a bid to
promote tourism trade."
</P>
<P>
Bali is located east of Java and has a population of more than
2.2 million, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said an agreement was expected to be signed after next
meeting scheduled to be held later this year. Final preparations
for the opening of the Bali route were also postponed until next
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait Airways Corporation now flies more than 30
destinations around the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
