<HEADLINE> South China Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The 81st China export commodity
trade fair did 1.645 billion US dollars worth of business since
its opening April 15 in Guangzhou, up 24 percent from the same
period of last year's fair.
</P>
<P>
Countries and regions doing the largest amount of business were
the European Union, Hong Kong and Macao, The United States,
Southeast Asia, Japan, and eight Gulf states.
</P>
<P>
The majority of 46 trade groups represented were from
Guangdong, Shanghai, China's special economic zones, and Jiangsu
and Shandong.
</P>
<P>
Some 26,000 business people from 135 countries and regions
attended the fair, 3.5 percent more than last fair. Most of them
are from countries and regions including the United States, Japan,
Germany, Republic of Korea, Singapore, Thailand, Italy, Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan.  
</P>
