<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Hungary To Enhance Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Hungary today
signed here an agreement on scientific and technological
cooperation as well as a memorandum of understanding (MOU) on
trade promotion cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Malaysian Science, Technology and
Environment Minister Law Hieng Ding and Hungarian Industry, Trade
and Tourism Minister Szabolcs Fazakas.
</P>
<P>
And the MOU was signed by Malaysian External Trade Development
Corporation (Maltrade) Director Mohd Abdul Halim and Hungarian
Investment and Trade Development Corporation Deputy General
Manager Mariann Farkas.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Hungarian Prime Minister Gyula Horn and his Malaysian
counterpart Mahathir Mohamad witnessed the signing after their
talks.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders discussed matters of mutual interest and how to
enhance bilateral cooperation in the economic field, acting
Foreign Minister Syed Hamid Albar said when briefing reporters on
the talks.
</P>
<P>
Hungary is interested in Malaysia's success in privatization
besides wanting to enhance bilateral ties in trade and economy,
said Syed Hamid, who is also defense minister.
</P>
<P>
Horn, who arrived here earlier today for a two-day official
visit, was also interested in Malaysia's success in environmental
protection and the Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC), the acting
foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
Syed Hamid said Hungary also offered its expertise and wide
experience in tourism development to Malaysia while wanting to
learn more about Malaysia's experience in developing technology
parks and industries.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian leader also invited Malaysian investors to
Hungary since there is only one Malaysian bank and one company
there.
</P>
<P>
Syed Hamid said Mahathir meanwhile wanted Hungary to be gateway
for Malaysian goods to East Europe while Malaysia for Hungarian
goods to the region.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian exports to Hungary last year totaled 146.6 million
ringgit (about 58.64 million U.S. dollars) while its imports from
Hungary totaled 48.6 million ringgit (about 5.04 million U.S.
dollars), he said.
</P>
<P>
Hungary is preparing for the visit of Malaysian King Tuanku
Jaafar and Queen Tuanku Najihah, according to Syed Hamid, who said
Horn also invited Mahathir to visit Hungary.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian prime minister earlier had a two-day private
visit to Langkawi, a tourist resort island in the northwest of
Malaysia before he flew into the capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
