<HEADLINE> BASF Opens Seventh Joint Venture in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The April 18 opening of the BASF
Shanghai Paint Co., Ltd. means increased investment from BASF AG,
the largest foreign investor in China's chemical industry.
</P>
<P>
The company was co-funded by Germany's BASF Lacke and Farben AG
and Shanghai Paint Co., Ltd, with 60 percent of the investment
coming from the former. It is BASF's seventh joint venture in
China.
</P>
<P>
The new company is expected to be a major paint supplier in
Asia and will provide the Asian market with automobile paint,
which has been imported from Europe.
</P>
<P>
Preparations started early last year and the company began
operation this January.
</P>
<P>
BASF AG is said to have invested one billion Deutsche marks in
China's chemical industry, and a tenth of its last year's 860
million marks in total sales came from production in China.
</P>
