<HEADLINE> Outlook Good For Economy in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua)-- Tibet faces an unprecedented good
opportunity for its economic and social development as more
assistance is called for to help this autonomous region, "China
Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Raidi, deputy-secretary of the Tibet Autonomous Regional
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party and chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Regional People's Congress made remarks
here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Tibetans should further emancipate their minds, speed up the
pace of reform and expand the openness in order to continue to
explore policies which help Tibet's economic growth, maintain its
stability and improve living standards of people in Tibet,
according to Raidi.
</P>
<P>
Raidi said at a ceremony marking the 10th anniversary of the
founding of Tibet Development Fund (TDF), China's first
non-governmental charity organization in the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.
</P>
<P>
Established in April 1987 at the initiative of two prominent
Tibetans - the 10th Panchen Lama and Ngapo Ngawang Jigme, the fund
is designed to launch disaster relief, cultural, education and
medical care and social welfare projects in Tibet and Tibetan
ethnic regions.
</P>
<P>
In the 10 years since its establishment, TDF has raised nearly
80 million yuan (9.6 million US dollars) in aid from both at home
amd abroad.  
</P>
