<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- I.K. Gujral, newly elected
leader of the 13-party United Front (UF), was sworn in as India's
12th prime minister here today, ending 22 days of political
uncertainty following the withdrawal of support by the Congress
Party to the Deve Gowda government.
</P>
<P>
Gowda lost the confidence vote in the Lower House on April 11.
The Congress withdrew its support to the Deve Gowda government on
March 30 for its failure to contain "communal force" in the
country and "tried its best to weaken the Congress".
</P>
<P>
The Congress, which had earlier staked claim to form the next
government following its withdrawal of support to the Gowda
government, changed its stance by declaring that it would support
a new leader of the UF.  
