<HEADLINE> North China Province Ties with Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
has achieved remarkable results in boosting economic cooperation
with Hong Kong, with trade volume reaching nearly 513 million US
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of Hong Kong-funded enterprises in the province now
stands at 2,622, costing a total of 6.6 billion US dollars in
investment. Of the enterprises, 2,286 are joint ventures and 208
are wholly-owned by Hong Kong business people.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 114 Hong Kong-invested enterprises with
investment ranging from 10 million to 30 million US dollars each,
and six with over 30 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
During recent years, the province has hosted various kinds of
investment and trade fairs in Hong Kong, expecting to tighten
cooperation between the two places.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has established close relationships
with some influenccial economic organizations in Hong Kong,
helping add channels for Hong Kong business people to pour
investment in the province.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that Hong Kong's return to the motherland is
expected to give a greater boost to economic contact between
them. 
