leather manufacturers join to reveal the industry's most
up-to-date production technology and a complete range of raw
materials, components, chemicals, accessories and machinery.
</P>
<P>
The show features 20 major pavilions among which Italy forms
the largest group with 435 exhibitors and Taiwan is the leading
pavilion among the Asian groups.
</P>
<P>
One hundred exhibitors from Thailand are present in the
two-phase fair to reflect the country has become one of the key
leather manufacturing base in the region.
</P>
<P>
The fair will continue with style and excitement in its second
part -- Fashion and Finished Products. More than 1,400 leading
leather manufacturers are coming from 37 countries and regions to
showcase their latest Fall-Winter leather fashion designs.
</P>
<P>
Spain, Turkey and Portugal will also bring to the visitors
fun-filled and inspiring fashion shows daily throughout the show
period. 
