<HEADLINE> 35 Sri Lankan Fishermen Held By India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-five Sri Lankan fishermen
were taken into custody by the Indian Coast Guard off Danushkodi
in south India Sunday, according to official sources today.
</P>
<P>
Seven fishing boats used by the fishermen were also detained by
the Indian Coast Guard. The boats worth Rs 14 million (241,000
U.S. dollars) were equipped with fishing sonars and have the
capability of staying out at sea for more than one day, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The boats belong to the Fatima Fishing Society in Pitipana,
Negombo, a town 25 kilometers north of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Several other Sri Lankan fishermen who were fishing close to
the detained boats had seen the Indian Coast Guard taking the Sri
Lankan boats into custody and reported the incident to the
authorities here, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
