<HEADLINE> United States Draw Mexico in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The United States forced
Mexico to a 2-2 draw in a crucial CONCACAF World Cup qualifier at
Foxboro, Massachusetts on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Mexican substitute headed the ball into his own goal in the
74th minute and that saved the American team from the brink of
defeat.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican team were reduced to 10 players as Luis
Hernandez was sent off for a tackle at the 59th minute.
</P>
<P>
Ramirez came on in the 64th minute. As the American team
pressed hard for the second equalizer, Ramirez tried to head away
a cross from Ernie Stewart. But the header was misdirected past
goal-keeper Adolfo Rios and bounced in off the left post.
</P>
<P>
The draw left Mexico on top of the group with eight points from
four games. The United States have garnered 5 points from one
win, two draws against one defeat.
</P>
<P>
The top three teams from the six-team final round of CONCACAF
zone advance to 1998 France World Cup finals. 
</P>
