<DOCNO> XIE19970421.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Plays Greater Role in China's Farming (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Science and technology are
playing a larger role in China's agriculture, as the country tries
to increase its grain production by a big margin.
</P>
<P>
The role of science and technology accounted for 39 percent
last year in contributing to agricultural development. Many
agriculture provinces have worked out policies to reinforce its
role.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi Province in mid-east China has called for contribution
from science and technology at 45 percent in the advancement of
agriculture this year. And Shandong, also in the east, has
guaranteed strong financial support for development of
agricultural science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Provinces of southern China have done their best to spread the
use of sparse-planting techniques for dry farmland, and sixty
percent of the grain production increase in east China's Fujian
Province has been attributed to the practice.
</P>
<P>
More than 260,000 ha of farmland in Zhejiang Province have been
planted using dry farmland techniques and tossing rice shoots.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi has added 260,000 ha of farmland on which cross-bred
rice varieties are sown, and more than 95 percent of Zhejiang's
farmland is covered with improved varieties of late rice.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
