<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Plays Greater Role in Chinese Farming (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- To increase farmers' awareness,
governments have taken practical measures to spread the use of
agro-techniques to remote rural areas. The technologies were
introduced to farmers through television, pamphlets, or training
classes sponsored by local government organizations.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Daxin, a farmer in Jiangxi's Zhoujiadun village, used to
suffer as his farmland produced less and less grain and his
orchard, little fruit.
</P>
<P>
But he got help from a provincial correspondence school, and
had a good harvest after applying what he had learned to
farming. His relatives and villagers soon rushed to follow his
example.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu Province has set up awards for successful applications
of research result and spreading the use of agro-techniques,
mainly to technicians at the grass-roots level.
</P>
<P>
Some provinces have increased input in agronomy and
technology. Shandong has allocated millions of US dollars for
improved varieties of crops like wheat, corn, and cotton, and
Anhui Province has worked out regulations on funding and
technician allocation.
</P>
<P>
Government efforts at various levels to revitalize agriculture
through the use of science and education have paid off, as it is
making continued contributions to the development of China's
agro-economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970421.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Airlines Told to Ground ATP Planes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
ordered Merpati Nusantara Airlines to ground its remaining fleet
of British-made advanced turbo prop (ATP) aircraft after one of
the planes crashed Saturday in South Sumatra, killing 15 people
and injuring 31 others.
</P>
<P>
Merpati spokesman Tondo Widodo said here Sunday night that
divestment of the remaining four aircraft would wait pending the
completion of the investigation into the crash.
</P>
<P>
The plane crashed on Belitung Island, 400 kilometers north of
Jakarta, at about 7:40 a.m. Saturday. The twin turbo prop
aircraft carried 52 passengers, including a crew of five and two
children and two babies.
</P>
<P>
Merpati, a subsidiary of national flag carrier Garuda
Indonesia, began flying the 68-seat ATP plane on short-distance
routes in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The black box of the ill-fated aircraft, which had been found
earlier, has been sent to Jakarta for studies and an investigation
team will determine whether the black box will be delivered to
England or Australia, official sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
