<HEADLINE> Foreign Firms Add Investment in Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 21 (Xinhua) -- More than ten multi-national
firms investing in Pudong New Area in Shanghai municipality made
additional investment in the area recently.
</P>
<P>
Their new addition has reached 500 million US dollars, 102
percent more than their original one, statistics from the local
foreign trade and economic cooperation bureau said.
</P>
<P>
These firms are doing so because they are encouraged by the
improvement of the investment environment, abundant profits and
bright prospects, said an analyst of the bureau.
</P>
<P>
Sharp Co. Ltd, for example, along with a Shanghai firm, has
invested nearly 30 million US dollars to produce air conditioners
in the area. The business volume for their products ranked first
in China's market.
</P>
<P>
Stimulated by great market potential and huge profits, the
corporation recently plans to add 120 million US dollars in the
area to produce refrigerators and washing machines. The new firm
is expected to produce 500,000 refrigerators and 500,000 washing
machines annualy after it went into operation this June.
</P>
<P>
It also set a long-term plan to produce one million air
conditioners and three million micro-wave ovens in the area by the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Pudong New Area, since its development seven years ago, has
witnessed increase in foreign investment. So far, 56
multi-national firms have carried out 104 investment projects in
the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
