<HEADLINE> Black Box of Ill-fated Indonesian Plane Discovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The black box of Indonesia's
Merpati Airline plane that crashed in Tanjung Pandan last Saturday
has been discovered, an airport official said.
</P>
<P>
The box has already been sent to Jakarta to be studied, Gatot
Sumarwan, head of the Administration Department of the Buluh
Tumbang Airport in Tanjung Pandan, Belitung Island, said Sunday,
according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Gatot Sumarwan also said that all the victims of the crash had
been established with the number of death victims remaining at 15.
</P>
<P>
The plane carried 52 passengers on board including five crew
members, he said.
</P>
<P>
The plane took off from Jakarta at 6:40 local time for
Belitung, South Sumatra, and it crashed at 7:39 about four
kilometers off Buluh Tumbang.
</P>
<P>
Merpati is a state-owned airline company which mostly operates
domestic services.  
</P>
