<HEADLINE> Zyuganov Reelected Russian Communist Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Communist Party
re-elected Gennady Zyuganov as its leader on Sunday after a
two-day congress, the Itar-Tass news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The congress, the party's first in four years, also adopted
documents on the party's strategy and tactics, and resolutions on
Zyuganov's political report as well as on the report "On Attitude
to the Ruling Political Regime in Russia."
</P>
<P>
In its resolution on the report "On Attitude to the Ruling
Political Regime in Russia," the party said that it stands for
national integrity and is against "offensive of private capital on
rights of the working people."
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the congress, Zyuganov said the party firmly stood
for "a union between Russia and Belarus" and would struggle to get
all-round support for its consolidation.
</P>
<P>
The congress was attended by about 400 Russian and foreign
representatives, and received a message of congratulation from
President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
The party, largest in Russia with more than 500,000 members,
commands the biggest faction in the State Duma (lower house of the
parliament). 
</P>
