<HEADLINE> China Wins Women's 4X100 Meters Medley Relay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOTHENBURG, Sweden, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China took the title
of the women's 4X100 meters medley relay in the world short-course
swimming championships here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese quartet narrowed missed their third relay world
record by clocking 3 minutes 57.83 seconds, just 0.10 of a second
outside their own world mark set in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese relay team led the race throughout while the German
team tried to narrow the gap over the backstroke and breaststroke
legs.
</P>
<P>
Misty Hyman put the American team into second place on the
butterfly leg but Le Jingyi kept China in front of her American
counterpart Jenny Thompson on the freestyle.
</P>
<P>
The American team finished second at 3:58.94, followed by
Australia in the third place at 4:01.55. 
</P>
</TEXT>
