<HEADLINE> Chen Yan Wins Women's 200 Meters Backstroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOTHENBURG, Sweden, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Chen Yan of China took
the title of the women's 200 meters backstroke on the final day of
the world short-course swimming championships.
</P>
<P>
American Misty Hyman led through the first 150 meters but Chen
stormed home and edged Hyman on the final stroke.
</P>
<P>
Chen's winning time is 2 minutes 7.50 seconds. Hyman was
second at 2:07.66.
</P>
<P>
Lea Oberstar of the United States took the bronze medal with a
time of 2:08.29. 
