<DOCNO> XIE19970421.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Right Extremists Mark Hitler's Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Right extremists marked Hitler's
birthday with scattered violence throughout Germany today, said
reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
In the eastern state of Saxony-Anhalt, four right extremists
were arrested by police after they attacked five immigrants from
former Soviet republics.
</P>
<P>
In the western German city of Ludwigshafen, a dormitory for
foreign refugees was torched by rightwing radicals, but no one was
injured.
</P>
<P>
Police also reported scattered violence by skinheads and other
rightwingers in the state of Thuringia. In one incident, a police
officer was injured after his car was attacked by a group of
radicals Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Police authorities in Gunzburg of Bavaria state today broke up
a rally by about 100 skinheads who had chanted Nazi slogans and
sung army songs of Nazi Germany's armed forces -- the Wehrmacht.
About 70 persons were detained and Nazi propaganda materials
confiscated.
</P>
<P>
Police in Dresden also detained 23 rightwing youngsters who had
held demonstrations in the streets and chanted Nazi slogans.
</P>
<P>
Adolf Hitler was born on April 20, 1889 in Braunau, Austria.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
